{Siegbert Tarrasch made a great effort to organise the first important German
chess tournament after the Great War. The best players took part, except for
the top two, Capablanca and Lasker. Their additional financial demands were
not accepted. The tournament was played in the Kurhaus of Baden-Baden from 15
iv until 20 v 1925. A super tournament had been played at the same place in
1870.   Alekhine had an amazing start of 91/2/10. He finished with twelve wins
and eight draws. Rubinstein could not keep up and scored 11/2 points less.   } 
